cancelFundRequest(uint256).details: Function to cancel a withdrawal request from a Arranger.

params.fundRequestId: The ID of the withdrawal request.

deposit(bytes32,address,uint256).details: Function for depositing tokens into a Fund Manager.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to deposit.
params.ilk: The unique identifier of the ilk.

drawFunds(address,uint256).details: Only the Arranger is authorized to call this function.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be drawn.
params.asset: The ERC20 token contract address from which funds are being drawn.

drawableFunds(address).details: Function to get the amount of funds that can be drawn by the Arranger.

returns.drawableFunds_: The amount of funds that can be drawn by the Arranger.

file(bytes32,address).details: Function to set a value in the contract, called by the admin.

params.what: The identifier for the value to be set.

getFundRequest(uint256).details: Returns a FundRequest struct at a given fundRequestId.

params.fundRequestId: The id of the fund request.

returns.fundRequest: The FundRequest struct at the fundRequestId.

getFundRequestsLength().details: Returns the length of the fundRequests array.

returns.fundRequestsLength: The length of the fundRequests array.

isCancelable(uint256).details: Function to check if a withdrawal request can be cancelled.

params.fundRequestId: The ID of the withdrawal request.

returns.isCancelable_: True if the withdrawal request can be cancelled, false otherwise.

maxWithdraw(bytes32,address).details: Function to get the maximum withdrawal possible for a specific asset and ilk.

params.ilk: The unique identifier of the ilk.

returns.maxWithdraw_: The maximum possible withdrawal for the asset.

requestFunds(bytes32,address,uint256,str.details: Function to initiate a withdrawal request from a Arranger.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to withdraw.
params.ilk: The unique identifier for a particular ilk.
params.info: Arbitrary string to provide additional info to the Arranger.

returns.fundRequestId: The ID of the withdrawal request.

withdraw(bytes32,address,uint256).details: Function for withdrawing tokens from a Fund Manager.

params.ilk: The unique identifier of the ilk.
params.maxAmount: The max amount of tokens to withdraw. Setting to "type(uint256).max" will ensure to withdraw all available liquidity.

drawFunds(address,uint256).notice: Draw funds from the contract to the Arranger.
